ARGUMENT

| Step | Hyp | Ref | Expression |
|---|---|---|---|

| 1 |  | ixxssxr.1 | |- O = ( x e. RR* , y e. RR* |-> { z e. RR* | ( x R z /\ z S y ) } ) |
| 2 |  | #P_anass | |- ( ( ( ( A e. RR* /\ B e. RR* ) /\ C e. RR* ) /\ ( A R C /\ C S B ) ) <-> ( ( A e. RR* /\ B e. RR* ) /\ ( C e. RR* /\ ( A R C /\ C S B ) ) ) ) |
| 3 |  | #P_df-3an | |- ( ( A e. RR* /\ B e. RR* /\ C e. RR* ) <-> ( ( A e. RR* /\ B e. RR* ) /\ C e. RR* ) ) |
| 4 | 3 | #P_anbi1i | |- ( ( ( A e. RR* /\ B e. RR* /\ C e. RR* ) /\ ( A R C /\ C S B ) ) <-> ( ( ( A e. RR* /\ B e. RR* ) /\ C e. RR* ) /\ ( A R C /\ C S B ) ) ) |
| 5 | 1 | #P_elmpt2cl | |- ( C e. ( A O B ) -> ( A e. RR* /\ B e. RR* ) ) |
| 6 | 1 | #P_elixx1 | |- ( ( A e. RR* /\ B e. RR* ) -> ( C e. ( A O B ) <-> ( C e. RR* /\ A R C /\ C S B ) ) ) |
| 7 |  | #P_3anass | |- ( ( C e. RR* /\ A R C /\ C S B ) <-> ( C e. RR* /\ ( A R C /\ C S B ) ) ) |
| 8 | 6, 7 | #P_syl6bb | |- ( ( A e. RR* /\ B e. RR* ) -> ( C e. ( A O B ) <-> ( C e. RR* /\ ( A R C /\ C S B ) ) ) ) |
| 9 | 5, 8 | #P_biadan2 | |- ( C e. ( A O B ) <-> ( ( A e. RR* /\ B e. RR* ) /\ ( C e. RR* /\ ( A R C /\ C S B ) ) ) ) |
| 10 | 2, 4, 9 | #P_3bitr4ri | |- ( C e. ( A O B ) <-> ( ( A e. RR* /\ B e. RR* /\ C e. RR* ) /\ ( A R C /\ C S B ) ) ) |
\
 Membership in a set of open intervals of extended reals.  We use the fact that an operation's value is empty outside of its domain to show ` A e. RR* ` and ` B e. RR* ` .  (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 3-Nov-2013.)
